description: My place is close to Brooklyn Botanical Gardens. You’ll love my place because of the coziness, the location, and the people. My place is good for couples, solo adventurers, business travelers, families (with kids), and furry friends (pets).

hosts.about:
Hello! 

My name is Sam. I am a New York Native living in Brooklyn. I originally grew up on a horse farm right out New York City. I love nature and the outdoors (hence why i'm across from the Botanical Gardens) Now I am here pursuing my dreams with my brother on working on opening up our families third flagship bakery.  I tried to make my apartment as cozy and rustic as my mother made our beautiful house upstate with exposed brick and wood beam ceilings. If you want to relax while being in the heart of Brooklyn while also being able to be in Manhattan in under 20 minutes come stay at my apartment!
